**BOUNDARY CONNECT**   
**DATABASE**

**Topology**

Databases ← VM \[has databases\] ← VM \[Boundary\] ← Client

**Tutorial**   
based this code  
[https://dev.azure.com/Botika/ilham-devops-intern-sandbox/\_git/ilham-devops-intern-sandbox](https://dev.azure.com/Botika/ilham-devops-intern-sandbox/_git/ilham-devops-intern-sandbox) 

1. Copy Boundary Information in /var/log/[boundary-init.sh](http://boundary-init.sh) in vm  
   ![][image1]  
2. Connect Boundary as Admin  
   ![][image2]  
3. Then save the Boundary token  
   ![][image3]  
4. Get Scope List (Global)  
   ![][image4]  
5. Get Scope List (Sub-Scope)  
   ![][image5]  
6. Create a TCP target to MySQL  
   ![][image6]  
7. Make connection to target  
   ![][image7]  
8. Connect to MySQL (port 3307\)  
   ![][image8]

**ENTRA ID**

9. Create enterprise application on Azure  
   [OIDC authentication with Microsoft Azure | Boundary | HashiCorp Developer](https://developer.hashicorp.com/boundary/tutorials/identity-management/oidc-azure#create-an-application)   
10. Then export Client ID, Client Secret, and Tenant ID as environment variables  
    ![][image9]  
11. Create OIDC auth method  
    ![][image10]  
12. Change state to active-public  
    ![][image11]  
13. Set OIDC as primary method  
    ![][image12]  
14. Authenticate using OIDC  
    ![][image13]  
    ![][image14]  
15. Create Roles for MySQL access  
    ![][image15]  
16. Grant access to role  
    ![][image16]  
17. Add Another permission to authorize session  
    ![][image17]  
18. Add users to role  
    ![][image18]  
19. Update the token to a token that authenticates with OIDC (Users token)  
    ![][image19]  
20. Create connection to MySQL again  
    ![][image20]  
21. Connect to Database  
    ![][image21]
